Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Police culture
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09lylpm
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 22 Jan 2018
Police culture, socialisation and identity. Laurie Taylor explores the process by which police officers become 'blue'. He's joined by Sarah Charman, a Reader in Criminology at the University of Portsmouth, Carol Cox, Acting Head of the School of Forensic and Applied Sciences at The University of Central Lancashire and Louise Westmarland, Professor of Criminology at the Open University. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less